<DocsLayout title="Migrations">
  <h2>Migrations</h2>
  <p>
    Migrations are guides for moving an existing project's chunk corpus
    forward when the workflow's principles, schema, or templates evolve.
    Each migration is a focused, reproducible procedure that converts the
    corpus into the current standard while preserving every chunk's
    architectural intent.
  </p>
  <p>
    Migrations are designed to be operator-led at the start and
    agent-driven at scale. You walk the first few chunks personally to
    build confidence in the agent's judgment, scale to small parallel
    waves once the pattern is clear, then hand off to full automation
    once the work is mechanical and the rules are tight.
  </p>

  <h3>Available migrations</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <a href="/docs/migrations/active-tense-chunks/">
        <strong>Active-tense chunks</strong>
      </a>
      &mdash; Migrate ACTIVE chunks to present-tense, system-centric framing.
      Catches retrospective <code>Currently, …</code> openings and chunk-centric
      <code>This chunk adds&hellip;</code> framing. Logs over-claims that need
      operator triage. Historicalizes chunks with no enduring intent.
    </li>
  </ul>
</DocsLayout>
